Heat a wok to a high temperature.Add the oil and when smoking add the romero pepper, vinegar, tomato ketchup, brown sugar and chilli. Stir fry for five minutes.Add the squid and honey and cook for a further two minutes.For the parsley oil, place the parsley, olive oil and lime juice in a small food processor and blend until smooth.To serve, place the squid stir-fry on a plate and drizzle over the parsley oil.